Date:12/3/2008 2:24:36 PM
From:E_K_S
Hi Grommit - It's some what scary as a lot of these preferred shares are priced
as if these companies are going bankrupt. The one reason I am attracted to
these types of shares is that with the current spread between the "TARP" funds
that banks can borrow and the current commercial mortgage rates, there should
be enough of an incentive (up to 900 basis points) for the banks to refinance
REIT debt. It will be interesting to watch what new type of lending is done in
the next 6-8 months. At some point this "TARP" money must find its way into the
debt market.

Currently, banks are still a bit timid to commit to new refinancing
obligations. When they eventually do a few of these deals, the market should
rally these preferred shares so that the yield reflects a more "normal" market
rate like 8%-12%.

