preferreds are cumulative so skipped div's have to be made up -- IF the company
survives enough to do so), but there will be preferreds (companies) that muddle
through. So I am hoping/expecting. And unless there's hyperinflation where
treasuries yield 8,12, 16 or more percent, these preferreds at current price
have got to be considered for a portfolio. Maybe not bought, but considered.
-g- . I'll be a buyer of some.

Here's where my preference would be a managed fund. The problem is these funds
use leverage to hype the yield and juice the assets (managers being paid on
assets under management, not on their fund's price performance). And that
leverage is in arcane (arcane to me anyway) stuff that's frozen or otherwise
scary.
