re Natural Gas.
I think that Natural Gas use for residential will increase over time but I do
not expect a short term boost First of all, installation costs are not trivial
so the current economic climate and second crude has become much cheaper too. A
big part

The way i see it, NG in NA is cyclical there are boom bust cycles with a
frequency of about 3 years. The way I see it this frequency may result by the
time it takes to get wells started, the infrastructure into place and the
decline (for most wells the throughput declines by 50% during the 1st year of
service). So if this is correct ( a big if in the current situation) then 2010
would be the time to invest.

XEC with decent management and low debt is not a bad bet, IMO. Serial diluter
like CHK may find themselves between a rock and hard place.
